title: A Phantom Sith
description:
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------


Before you see the next installment in the Star Wars saga get ready to watch the
prequel trilogy as you have never seen it before....as a single movie with a running
time on par with all other films and edited together in a way to tell one cohesive 
story. Inspired by the Topher Grace 88-minute cut, this version offers a unique 
take on the trilogy telling a tigher narrative and providing the best possible ending.

FORMAT.......................: MOV
CODEC........................: H.264
GENRE........................: Action
FILE SIZE....................: 4.96 GB
RESOLUTION...................: 1280*720
FRAME RATE...................: 30 fps
BITRATE......................: 4992 kbps
LANGUAGE.....................: English
SUBTITLES....................: None
RUNTIME......................: 138 mins

TO FIX AUDIO SYNC
1) Use VLC Media Player
2) Tools > Track Synchronization
3) Set Audio track synchronization to: -0.4000 (Hastened)
This will sync the audio as the render framerate is different than source; sorry.



Part I-III in George Lucas' epic, Star Wars: A Phantom Sith opens with a prologue of Obi-Wan, Qui-Gon, and Darth Maul. The plot then jumps later to Obi-Wan keeping his promise to Qui-Gon to train the one who will bring balace to the force. The story then follows the life of Anakin Skywalker, a Padawan, as he learns the ways of the Jedi, as he and his allies (Obi-Wan, Senator Amidala, Yoda, Mace Windu, R2-D2, and C-3PO), attempt to stop corruption in the Senate, all the while keeping his love with Senator Amidala a secret. The conclusion is cluminated with Order 66, phantom Sith rising, and the birth of twins, the Galactice Empire, and Lord Darth Vader
